#Use the print() function to format the words “Name”, “Is”, and “James” so they appear with three asterisks (***) between them.
#Strings: "Name", "Is", "James"
print("Name", "Is", "James",sep='***')
#sep= ' ' an optional keyword argument used exclusively inside the built-in print() function to specify how multiple items should be separated in the console output. By default, Python separates multiple arguments passed to print() with a single whitespace character (" ").